# Architecture & Directory Rules

Next.js App Router PWA for farm management. **Feature-based (domain-driven)** layout. Do not invent new top-level folders or put domain logic in `lib/`.

## `app/` — Routing only

- Only: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, route handlers, `globals.css`.
- No heavy business logic or large UI here — import from `features/` or `components/layout/`.
- Route groups: `(authentication)` (login), `(dashboard)` (app shell).
- Root `proxy.ts` for route protection (not `middleware.ts`).

## `features/` — Domain / business logic

One folder per module: `auth`, `dashboard`, `production`, `cages`, etc.

| Subfolder | Use for |
|-----------|---------|
| `components/` | UI only for this feature |
| `actions/` | Server Actions (mutations, form submits) |
| `services/` | DB helpers, domain operations (e.g. `create-user.ts`) |
| `server/` | Server-only config wired to a library (e.g. Better Auth) |
| `client/` | Client-only config (e.g. auth client) |
| `lib/` | Feature helpers (session, permissions, password hashing) |
| `config/` | Static config (nav items, constants) |
| `schemas/` | Zod schemas for this feature |
| `*.test.ts(x)` | Colocated unit tests (Bun) — see `testing-standards.mdc` |

Example: `features/auth/actions/sign-in.ts`, `features/auth/server/auth.ts`, `features/dashboard/config/navigation.ts`.

## `components/` — Global presentation

| Subfolder | Use for |
|-----------|---------|
| `ui/` | shadcn primitives — avoid edits unless asked |
| `shared/` | Reusable across domains (tables, badges, loaders) |
| `layout/` | App shell (sidebar, header, theme switcher wrappers) |
| `providers/` | App-wide providers (theme, navigation progress) |

## `lib/` — Global infrastructure only

- `prisma.ts`, `utils.ts` (`cn`), etc.
- **No** domain logic, feature services, or entity CRUD.

## Placement checklist

1. Used across multiple domains? → `components/shared/` or `components/layout/`
2. Single feature only? → `features/[name]/components/`
3. Form submit / mutation? → `features/[name]/actions/`
4. Domain DB operation? → `features/[name]/services/`
5. Raw client singleton / generic util? → `lib/`
